<p class="">I am coming to that too, as we are going to have this out— <blockquote><q>"because the spirit of the British Army has to be regained."</q></blockquote> The Prime Minister appointed first General Gott, who tragically lost his life, and then General Montgomery. The hon. Member continued: <blockquote><q>"We have in this country five or six generals, members of other nations, Czechs, Poles, and French, all of them trained in the use of German weapons and German technique."</q></blockquote><span id="464" class="column-number" data-column-number="464"></span> So he described their unfortunate reverses: <blockquote><q>"I know it is hurtful to our pride but would it not be possible to put some of these men temporarily in the field?"</q></blockquote> His attitude at that time was a Polish General instead of General Montgomery. In order to complete the quotation——</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
