        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-aa5fd2f1-f822-4fd7-80c2-deccaefefb63">
                Mr. Cocks
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-aa5fd2f1-f822-4fd7-80c2-deccaefefb63" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1945-01-18/debates/0c4b38dc-56db-44e2-8661-51bf83e842a1/WarSituationAndForeignPolicy#contribution-aa5fd2f1-f822-4fd7-80c2-deccaefefb63">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">Surely, the principle is that anybody can have any Government they like, except a Fascist one.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-aa5fd2f1-f822-4fd7-80c2-deccaefefb63" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1945-01-18/debates/0c4b38dc-56db-44e2-8661-51bf83e842a1/WarSituationAndForeignPolicy#contribution-aa5fd2f1-f822-4fd7-80c2-deccaefefb63">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>





<div class="content-item" id="contribution-4219b49d-0219-4131-9790-55f8098a0b71">
    <div class="col-md-9 edit-fail-error">
        <div class="alert alert-danger" id="alert-4219b49d-0219-4131-9790-55f8098a0b71">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-9 multiple-edit-warning">
        <div class="alert alert-warning" id="warning-4219b49d-0219-4131-9790-55f8098a0b71">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-4219b49d-0219-4131-9790-55f8098a0b71">
                Mr. Attlee
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-4219b49d-0219-4131-9790-55f8098a0b71" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1945-01-18/debates/0c4b38dc-56db-44e2-8661-51bf83e842a1/WarSituationAndForeignPolicy#contribution-4219b49d-0219-4131-9790-55f8098a0b71">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">It is not a question of a Fascist, but of a Right-Wing, Government. Do not fall into the error of the hon. Member for West Fife, of thinking that everybody who is Right-Wing is Fascist. They may be old-fashioned monarchists, Catholics, and the like. Do not let Hitler get away with it by giving him too many companions. Therefore, I say that we were right to see that the Greeks got a fair chance with their own Government. I would ask hon. Members to get away from that typical British habit of dealing with the Balkans by falling in love with one party or one nationality. It is very difficult to get knowledge of all the facts. I would say that, on the record of this Government and on the known opinions of this Government, we have the right to be trusted to carry out the principles in which we believe.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-4219b49d-0219-4131-9790-55f8098a0b71" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1945-01-18/debates/0c4b38dc-56db-44e2-8661-51bf83e842a1/WarSituationAndForeignPolicy#contribution-4219b49d-0219-4131-9790-55f8098a0b71">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>





